{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840785815,"sessionID":"ses_287a5146bffeTh6Iwja2M3hcHz","part":{"id":"prt_d785b5d00001zhaFhbiP72v3Sm","messageID":"msg_d785b47e2001z5TOLEWVe7gChF","sessionID":"ses_287a5146bffeTh6Iwja2M3hcHz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_09e4cc609a924e5e869d8948","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Design Document: CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n## AR-003 — CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n**Module**: `pkg/apis`  \n**Language**: Go  \n**API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n**Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n**Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\n### Module Structure\n\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n├── doc.go           # Package documentation with group/version markers\n├── register.go      # Scheme registration and GroupVersion constants\n├── types.go         # CRD type definitions\n├── types_test.go    # Unit tests\n└── zz_generated.deepcopy.go  # Auto-generated deepcopy methods\n```\n\n### Design Principles\n\n- **Kubernetes Native**: Follows standard Kubernetes CRD patterns using `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`\n- **Minimal Coupling**: Shared types are defined in a dedicated package to be used by both the API server and client-go\n- **Kubebuilder Markers**: Uses kubebuilder annotations for code generation (controller-gen, client-gen)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Core CRD Types\n\n#### AgentRuntime\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `TypeMeta` | `metav1.TypeMeta` | APIVersion and Kind |\n| `ObjectMeta` | `metav1.ObjectMeta` | Standard metadata (name, namespace, etc.) |\n| `Spec` | `AgentRuntimeSpec` | Desired state |\n| `Status` | `AgentRuntimeStatus` | Observed state |\n\n**Short Name**: `ar`\n\n#### CodeInterpreter\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `TypeMeta` | `metav1.TypeMeta` | APIVersion and Kind |\n| `ObjectMeta` | `metav1.ObjectMeta` | Standard metadata |\n| `Spec` | `CodeInterpreterSpec` | Desired state |\n| `Status` | `CodeInterpreterStatus` | Observed state |\n\n**Short Name**: `ci`\n\n### 2.2 Specification Types\n\n#### AgentRuntimeSpec\n\n| Field | Validation | Default | Description |\n|-------|------------|---------|-------------|\n| `MaxSessionDuration` | Required, Pattern: `^(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$` | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session duration |\n| `SessionTimeout` | Required, Pattern: `^(\\d+m)|(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$` | `\"15m\"` | Session timeout |\n| `TargetPorts` | Required, MinItems=1 | - | Port configuration |\n| `PodTemplate` | Optional | `nil` | Custom Pod specification |\n\n#### CodeInterpreterSpec\n\n| Field | Validation | Default | Description |\n|-------|------------|---------|-------------|\n| `AuthMode` | Enum: `picod`, `none` | `\"picod\"` | Authentication mode |\n| `MaxSessionDuration` | Pattern: `^(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$` | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session duration |\n| `SessionTimeout` | Pattern: `^(\\d+m)|(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$` | `\"15m\"` | Session timeout |\n| `Ports` | MinItems=0 | `[]` | Port configuration |\n| `Template` | Required | - | Container specification |\n| `WarmPoolSize` | Default=0 | `0` | Pre-warmed instance pool size |\n\n### 2.3 Shared Types\n\n#### TargetPort\n\n| Field | Validation | Description |\n|-------|------------|-------------|\n| `Port` | Required, Range: 1-65535 | Port number |\n| `Protocol` | Required, Enum: `HTTP`, `HTTPS` | Protocol type |\n| `Name` | Optional | Port name |\n| `PathPrefix` | Optional | URL path prefix |\n\n#### PodTemplateSpec\n\nWraps `metav1.ObjectMeta` and a subset of `corev1.PodSpec` for custom pod configuration.\n\n#### PodSpec\n\nSelective subset of `corev1.PodSpec` including:\n- Containers, InitContainers\n- Volumes, VolumeMounts\n- Resource requirements\n- Security settings\n- Scheduling options (NodeSelector, Affinity, Tolerations)\n- DNS and network settings\n\n#### ContainerSpec\n\nSubset of `corev1.Container` including:\n- Image, Command, Args\n- Environment variables\n- Resource limits\n- Probes (Liveness, Readiness, Startup)\n- Security context\n\n#### ContainerTemplateSpec\n\nSimplified container spec for CodeInterpreter:\n- Image (Required)\n- Command, Args\n- Env\n- Resources\n- RuntimeClassName\n\n#### AuthMode\n\n```go\nconst (\n    AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"\n    AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"\n)\n```\n\n### 2.4 Status Types\n\n#### AgentRuntimeStatus\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `Conditions` | `[]metav1.Condition` | Kubernetes conditions |\n| `ObservedGeneration` | `int64` | Last reconciled generation |\n\n#### CodeInterpreterStatus\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `Conditions` | `[]metav1.Condition` | Kubernetes conditions |\n| `ObservedGeneration` | `int64` | Last reconciled generation |\n| `Ready` | `bool` | Readiness indicator |\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Group Version Resource\n\n```go\nconst (\n    GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n)\n\nvar SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: GroupName, Version: Version}\n```\n\n### 3.2 REST Resources\n\n| CRD | Plural | Short Name | Scope |\n|-----|--------|------------|-------|\n| AgentRuntime | `agentruntimes` | `ar` | Namespaced |\n| CodeInterpreter | `codeinterpreters` | `ci` | Namespaced |\n\n### 3.3 Subresources\n\nBoth CRDs support the `status` subresource for status updates without modifying spec.\n\n### 3.4 Custom Resource Definitions\n\nGenerated via `controller-gen` using kubebuilder markers:\n- `+genclient`: Generate client code\n- `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`: List type marker\n- `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`: Enable status subresource\n- `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName=...`: Short names for CLI\n- `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`: Custom columns for `kubectl get`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Validation Errors\n\nField validation uses kubebuilder markers:\n- **Required fields**: `+kubebuilder:validation:Required`\n- **Pattern matching**: Regex patterns for time durations\n- **Enums**: Explicit value lists\n- **Range validation**: Min/Max for numeric fields\n\nInvalid resources are rejected by the API server with detailed validation errors.\n\n### 4.2 Conditions\n\nStandard Kubernetes condition patterns:\n- `metav1.Condition` with Type, Status, Reason, Message, LastTransitionTime\n- Conditions are set by controllers to indicate resource state\n\n---\n\n## 5. Constants\n\n### 5.1 Group and Version\n\n```go\nconst (\n    GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n)\n```\n\n### 5.2 Auth Modes\n\n```go\nconst (\n    AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"\n    AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"\n)\n```\n\n### 5.3 Default Values\n\n| Field | Default |\n|-------|---------|\n| `MaxSessionDuration` | `\"8h\"` |\n| `SessionTimeout` | `\"15m\"` |\n| `AuthMode` | `\"picod\"` |\n| `WarmPoolSize` | `0` |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Tests (`types_test.go`)\n\n- DeepCopy verification for all types\n- Scheme registration validation\n- Default value verification\n\n### 6.2 Code Generation\n\n- **controller-gen**: Generates CRD manifests and RBAC\n- **client-gen**: Generates typed client, informers, listers\n- **deepcopy-gen**: Generates `DeepCopyInto` methods\n\n### 6.3 Integration Testing\n\n- Create/update/delete operations via client-go\n- Status subresource updates\n- Validation webhook tests\n\n---\n\n## 7. Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | v0.34.x | Core Kubernetes types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.x | Metadata and runtime |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | v0.34.x | Code generation tools |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Regeneration\n\n```bash\nmake gen      # Run controller-gen + code-generator\n# Or individually:\ncontroller-gen crd:crdVersions=v1 paths=\"./...\" output:crd:artifacts:config=config/crd/bases\nhack/update-codegen.sh\n```","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775840785808,"end":1775840785812}}}}
