{"type":"text","timestamp":1775840822147,"sessionID":"ses_287a5146bffeTh6Iwja2M3hcHz","part":{"id":"prt_d785c7f34001eSVVFHVRJTuUng","messageID":"msg_d785c56fe0019U36YUDlhckY1P","sessionID":"ses_287a5146bffeTh6Iwja2M3hcHz","type":"text","text":"Now I understand - there's already a design.md with comprehensive content for AR-001. I need to add content specifically for AR-003 (shared types and constants). Let me add a focused section:","time":{"start":1775840822144,"end":1775840822144}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840867800,"sessionID":"ses_287a5146bffeTh6Iwja2M3hcHz","part":{"id":"prt_d785c8382001Qu6js2iYT8avhm","messageID":"msg_d785c56fe0019U36YUDlhckY1P","sessionID":"ses_287a5146bffeTh6Iwja2M3hcHz","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_26309e6ef60e4d5bb26068bb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","newString":"## Build Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `make generate` | Run controller-gen to produce deepcopy functions |\n| `make gen-crd` | Generate CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n| `make gen-client` | Generate client-go to `client-go/` |\n| `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Verify types compile |\n\n---\n\n# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-003 focuses on the shared types and constants used across AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. These shared definitions ensure consistency and reduce duplication across the API.\n\n## Module Structure\n\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n├── doc.go                    # Package documentation + kubebuilder markers\n├── register.go               # GroupVersion constants and scheme registration\n├── types.go                  # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, shared types)\n├── types_test.go             # Unit tests\n└── zz_generated.deepcopy.go  # Auto-generated deepcopy methods\n```\n\n## Shared Constants\n\n### Group Version\n\n```go\nconst (\n    GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n)\n\nvar SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: GroupName, Version: Version}\n```\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `GroupName` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | API group name |\n| `Version` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | API version |\n| `SchemeGroupVersion` | `schema.GroupVersion` | Combined GroupVersion for scheme registration |\n\n### Auth Modes\n\n```go\ntype AuthMode string\n\nconst (\n    AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"  // picod authentication\n    AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"   // No authentication\n)\n```\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `AuthModePicod` | `\"picod\"` | Use picod for session authentication |\n| `AuthModeNone` | `\"none\"` | No authentication required |\n\n## Shared Types\n\n### TargetPort\n\nDefines port configuration for runtime services.\n\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    Port       int32  `json:\"port\"`        // Required: 1-65535\n    Protocol   string `json:\"protocol\"`    // Required: HTTP or HTTPS\n    Name       string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### PodTemplateSpec\n\nCustom pod template for runtime pods.\n\n```go\ntype PodTemplateSpec struct {\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec              *PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### PodSpec\n\nSelective subset of `corev1.PodSpec` for runtime customization.\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `Containers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Container specifications |\n| `Volumes` | `[]corev1.Volume` | Pod volumes |\n| `RestartPolicy` | `corev1.RestartPolicy` | Container restart policy |\n| `ServiceAccountName` | `string` | Service account for pods |\n| `NodeSelector` | `map[string]string` | Node selection criteria |\n| `Affinity` | `*corev1.Affinity` | Pod scheduling affinity |\n| `Tolerations` | `[]corev1.Toleration` | Node taint tolerations |\n| `PriorityClassName` | `string` | Priority class |\n| `Priority` | `*int32` | Priority value |\n| `DNSPolicy` | `corev1.DNSPolicy` | DNS configuration |\n| `HostNetwork` | `bool` | Use host network |\n| `HostPID` | `bool` | Use host PID namespace |\n| `HostIPC` | `bool` | Use host IPC namespace |\n| `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.PodSecurityContext` | Pod security context |\n| `ImagePullSecrets` | `[]corev1.LocalObjectReference` | Image pull secrets |\n| `InitContainers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Init containers |\n\n### ContainerSpec\n\nSelective subset of `corev1.Container`.\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `Name` | `string` | Container name (Required) |\n| `Image` | `string` | Container image (Required) |\n| `Command` | `[]string` | Entrypoint command |\n| `Args` | `[]string` | Command arguments |\n| `Env` | `[]corev1.EnvVar` | Environment variables |\n| `Resources` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements` | Compute resources |\n| `ImagePullPolicy` | `corev1.PullPolicy` | Image pull policy |\n| `Ports` | `[]corev1.ContainerPort` | Exposed ports |\n| `LivenessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Liveness probe |\n| `ReadinessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Readiness probe |\n| `StartupProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Startup probe |\n| `VolumeMounts` | `[]corev1.VolumeMount` | Volume mounts |\n| `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.SecurityContext` | Container security context |\n\n### ContainerTemplateSpec\n\nSimplified container spec for CodeInterpreter.\n\n```go\ntype ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n    Image            string                    `json:\"image\"` // Required\n    Command          []string                  `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n    Args             []string                  `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    Env              []corev1.EnvVar           `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n    Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n    RuntimeClassName *string                   `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Scheme Registration\n\n### Resource Helper\n\n```go\nfunc Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource {\n    return SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(resource).GroupResource()\n}\n```\n\nReturns `GroupResource` for RBAC and storage configuration.\n\n### Type Registration\n\n```go\nfunc AddKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n    scheme.AddKnownTypes(SchemeGroupVersion,\n        &AgentRuntime{},\n        &AgentRuntimeList{},\n        &CodeInterpreter{},\n        &CodeInterpreterList{},\n    )\n    metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n## Default Values\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Applied By |\n|-------|------|---------|------------|\n| `MaxSessionDuration` | `string` | `\"8h\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n| `SessionTimeout` | `string` | `\"15m\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n| `AuthMode` | `AuthMode` | `\"picod\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n| `WarmPoolSize` | `int32` | `0` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n\n## Usage by CRDs\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n- Uses: `TargetPort`, `PodTemplateSpec`, `PodSpec`, `ContainerSpec`\n- Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`\n\n### CodeInterpreter\n\n- Uses: `TargetPort`, `ContainerTemplateSpec`, `AuthMode`\n- Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`, `AuthModePicod`, `AuthModeNone`\n\n## Code Generation\n\nTypes are annotated with kubebuilder markers for code generation:\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n```\n\n| Marker | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `+genclient` | Generate typed client |\n| `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` | Generate list type |\n| `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` | Enable status subresource |\n| `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName` | CLI short name |\n| `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` | Custom columns |\n\n## Validation\n\nShared types use kubebuilder validation markers:\n\n| Validation | Marker | Applied To |\n|------------|--------|------------|\n| Required | `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` | Port, Protocol, Image |\n| Pattern | `+kubebuilder:validation:Pattern` | Duration strings |\n| Enum | `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum` | AuthMode, Protocol |\n| Range | `+kubebuilder:validation:Minimum/Maximum` | Port number |\n| MinItems | `+kubebuilder:validation:MinItems` | TargetPorts array |","oldString":"## Build Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `make generate` | Run controller-gen to produce deepcopy functions |\n| `make gen-crd` | Generate CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n| `make gen-client` | Generate client-go to `client-go/` |\n| `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Verify types compile |"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\n@@ -355,5 +355,223 @@\n |---------|-------------|\n | `make generate` | Run controller-gen to produce deepcopy functions |\n | `make gen-crd` | Generate CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n | `make gen-client` | Generate client-go to `client-go/` |\n-| `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Verify types compile |\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+| `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Verify types compile |\n+\n+---\n+\n+# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n+\n+## Overview\n+\n+AR-003 focuses on the shared types and constants used across AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. These shared definitions ensure consistency and reduce duplication across the API.\n+\n+## Module Structure\n+\n+```\n+pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n+├── doc.go                    # Package documentation + kubebuilder markers\n+├── register.go               # GroupVersion constants and scheme registration\n+├── types.go                  # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, shared types)\n+├── types_test.go             # Unit tests\n+└── zz_generated.deepcopy.go  # Auto-generated deepcopy methods\n+```\n+\n+## Shared Constants\n+\n+### Group Version\n+\n+```go\n+const (\n+    GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n+    Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n+)\n+\n+var SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: GroupName, Version: Version}\n+```\n+\n+| Constant | Value | Description |\n+|----------|-------|-------------|\n+| `GroupName` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | API group name |\n+| `Version` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | API version |\n+| `SchemeGroupVersion` | `schema.GroupVersion` | Combined GroupVersion for scheme registration |\n+\n+### Auth Modes\n+\n+```go\n+type AuthMode string\n+\n+const (\n+    AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"  // picod authentication\n+    AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"   // No authentication\n+)\n+```\n+\n+| Constant | Value | Description |\n+|----------|-------|-------------|\n+| `AuthModePicod` | `\"picod\"` | Use picod for session authentication |\n+| `AuthModeNone` | `\"none\"` | No authentication required |\n+\n+## Shared Types\n+\n+### TargetPort\n+\n+Defines port configuration for runtime services.\n+\n+```go\n+type TargetPort struct {\n+    Port       int32  `json:\"port\"`        // Required: 1-65535\n+    Protocol   string `json:\"protocol\"`    // Required: HTTP or HTTPS\n+    Name       string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n+    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### PodTemplateSpec\n+\n+Custom pod template for runtime pods.\n+\n+```go\n+type PodTemplateSpec struct {\n+    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n+    Spec              *PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### PodSpec\n+\n+Selective subset of `corev1.PodSpec` for runtime customization.\n+\n+| Field | Type | Description |\n+|-------|------|-------------|\n+| `Containers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Container specifications |\n+| `Volumes` | `[]corev1.Volume` | Pod volumes |\n+| `RestartPolicy` | `corev1.RestartPolicy` | Container restart policy |\n+| `ServiceAccountName` | `string` | Service account for pods |\n+| `NodeSelector` | `map[string]string` | Node selection criteria |\n+| `Affinity` | `*corev1.Affinity` | Pod scheduling affinity |\n+| `Tolerations` | `[]corev1.Toleration` | Node taint tolerations |\n+| `PriorityClassName` | `string` | Priority class |\n+| `Priority` | `*int32` | Priority value |\n+| `DNSPolicy` | `corev1.DNSPolicy` | DNS configuration |\n+| `HostNetwork` | `bool` | Use host network |\n+| `HostPID` | `bool` | Use host PID namespace |\n+| `HostIPC` | `bool` | Use host IPC namespace |\n+| `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.PodSecurityContext` | Pod security context |\n+| `ImagePullSecrets` | `[]corev1.LocalObjectReference` | Image pull secrets |\n+| `InitContainers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Init containers |\n+\n+### ContainerSpec\n+\n+Selective subset of `corev1.Container`.\n+\n+| Field | Type | Description |\n+|-------|------|-------------|\n+| `Name` | `string` | Container name (Required) |\n+| `Image` | `string` | Container image (Required) |\n+| `Command` | `[]string` | Entrypoint command |\n+| `Args` | `[]string` | Command arguments |\n+| `Env` | `[]corev1.EnvVar` | Environment variables |\n+| `Resources` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements` | Compute resources |\n+| `ImagePullPolicy` | `corev1.PullPolicy` | Image pull policy |\n+| `Ports` | `[]corev1.ContainerPort` | Exposed ports |\n+| `LivenessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Liveness probe |\n+| `ReadinessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Readiness probe |\n+| `StartupProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Startup probe |\n+| `VolumeMounts` | `[]corev1.VolumeMount` | Volume mounts |\n+| `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.SecurityContext` | Container security context |\n+\n+### ContainerTemplateSpec\n+\n+Simplified container spec for CodeInterpreter.\n+\n+```go\n+type ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n+    Image            string                    `json:\"image\"` // Required\n+    Command          []string                  `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n+    Args             []string                  `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n+    Env              []corev1.EnvVar           `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n+    Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n+    RuntimeClassName *string                   `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+## Scheme Registration\n+\n+### Resource Helper\n+\n+```go\n+func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource {\n+    return SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(resource).GroupResource()\n+}\n+```\n+\n+Returns `GroupResource` for RBAC and storage configuration.\n+\n+### Type Registration\n+\n+```go\n+func AddKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n+    scheme.AddKnownTypes(SchemeGroupVersion,\n+        &AgentRuntime{},\n+        &AgentRuntimeList{},\n+        &CodeInterpreter{},\n+        &CodeInterpreterList{},\n+    )\n+    metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n+    return nil\n+}\n+```\n+\n+## Default Values\n+\n+| Field | Type | Default | Applied By |\n+|-------|------|---------|------------|\n+| `MaxSessionDuration` | `string` | `\"8h\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n+| `SessionTimeout` | `string` | `\"15m\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n+| `AuthMode` | `AuthMode` | `\"picod\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n+| `WarmPoolSize` | `int32` | `0` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n+\n+## Usage by CRDs\n+\n+### AgentRuntime\n+\n+- Uses: `TargetPort`, `PodTemplateSpec`, `PodSpec`, `ContainerSpec`\n+- Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`\n+\n+### CodeInterpreter\n+\n+- Uses: `TargetPort`, `ContainerTemplateSpec`, `AuthMode`\n+- Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`, `AuthModePicod`, `AuthModeNone`\n+\n+## Code Generation\n+\n+Types are annotated with kubebuilder markers for code generation:\n+\n+```go\n+// +genclient\n+// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n+// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n+// +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar\n+// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n+```\n+\n+| Marker | Purpose |\n+|--------|---------|\n+| `+genclient` | Generate typed client |\n+| `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` | Generate list type |\n+| `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` | Enable status subresource |\n+| `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName` | CLI short name |\n+| `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` | Custom columns |\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+Shared types use kubebuilder validation markers:\n+\n+| Validation | Marker | Applied To |\n+|------------|--------|------------|\n+| Required | `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` | Port, Protocol, Image |\n+| Pattern | `+kubebuilder:validation:Pattern` | Duration strings |\n+| Enum | `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum` | AuthMode, Protocol |\n+| Range | `+kubebuilder:validation:Minimum/Maximum` | Port number |\n+| MinItems | `+kubebuilder:validation:MinItems` | TargetPorts array |\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","before":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- Go module path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs are defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`. These types enable the AgentCube control plane to manage sandbox runtime configurations programmatically through the Kubernetes API server.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐\n│   API Server        │      │   Workload Manager  │\n│                     │      │                     │\n│  ┌───────────────┐  │      │  ┌───────────────┐  │\n│  │ agentruntimes │  │◄─────│  │ CREATE/UPDATE │  │\n│  └───────────────┘  │      │  └───────────────┘  │\n│  ┌───────────────┐  │      └─────────────────────┘\n│  │codeinterpreters│ │\n│  └───────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────┘\n           │\n           ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐\n│   client-go         │\n│   (generated)       │\n│                     │\n│ - Typed clients     │\n│ - Listers           │\n│ - Informers         │\n└─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Package Structure\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `doc.go` | Package documentation, kubebuilder markers |\n| `groupversion_info.go` | GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder |\n| `register.go` | Kind constants, resource helpers |\n| `types.go` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n| `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | DeepCopy methods (generated) |\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec              AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status            AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n    PodTemplate *PodTemplateSpec `json:\"podTemplate,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreter\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec              CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status            CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    AuthMode *AuthMode `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n    SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n    Ports []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Template ContainerTemplateSpec `json:\"template\"`\n    WarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n    Ready bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Shared Types\n\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"` // HTTP or HTTPS\n    Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype PodTemplateSpec struct {\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec PodSpecSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype PodSpecSpec struct {\n    // Selective PodSpec fields: Containers, Volumes, ImagePullSecrets, etc.\n    // See proposal.md for full field list.\n}\n\ntype ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n    Image string `json:\"image\"`\n    Command []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n    Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n    Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n    RuntimeClassName *string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AuthMode string\n\nconst (\n    AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"\n    AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"\n)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `*metav1.Duration` | Yes | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `*metav1.Duration` | Yes | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout before cleanup |\n| `targetPort` | `[]TargetPort` | Yes | - | Port configuration array |\n| `podTemplate` | `*PodTemplateSpec` | No | - | Pod specification overrides |\n\n### CodeInterpreter\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `authMode` | `*AuthMode` | No | `\"picod\"` | Authentication mode: `picod`, `none` |\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `*metav1.Duration` | No | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `*metav1.Duration` | No | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout |\n| `ports` | `[]TargetPort` | No | - | Port configuration |\n| `template` | `ContainerTemplateSpec` | Yes | - | Container specification |\n| `warmPoolSize` | `*int32` | No | `0` | Pre-warmed pod count |\n\n### Status Subresource\n\nBoth CRDs support `/status` subresource:\n- `conditions`: Kubernetes conditions array\n- `observedGeneration`: Last reconciled generation\n\nCodeInterpreter additionally includes:\n- `ready`: Boolean readiness indicator\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### CRD Validation\n\nValidation rules embedded via kubebuilder markers:\n\n```go\n// Required field validation\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n\n// Default value handling\n// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n\n// Enum validation (AuthMode)\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n```\n\n### Client-go Error Handling\n\nStandard Kubernetes client errors are handled by client-go:\n\n| Error Type | Handling |\n|------------|----------|\n| `errors.IsNotFound` | Resource does not exist |\n| `errors.IsAlreadyExists` | Resource already exists |\n| `errors.IsConflict` | Optimistic lock failure |\n| `errors.IsTimeout` | Operation timeout |\n\nExample usage:\n\n```go\nagentRuntime, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\nif errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n    // Handle not found\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Type Validation\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeSpecValidation(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        spec    AgentRuntimeSpec\n        wantErr bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"valid spec with all required fields\",\n            spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n                SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n                Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n            },\n            wantErr: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"missing required maxSessionDuration\",\n            spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                SessionTimeout: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n                Ports:          []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n            },\n            wantErr: true,\n        },\n    }\n\n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            // Validate using Kubernetes validation webhook or custom validation\n            err := validateAgentRuntimeSpec(tt.spec)\n            if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n                t.Errorf(\"validateAgentRuntimeSpec() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### DeepCopy Verification\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n    original := &AgentRuntime{\n        Spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n            SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n            Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\"}},\n        },\n    }\n\n    copy := original.DeepCopy()\n\n    // Verify copy is independent\n    copy.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration = 10 * time.Hour\n\n    if original.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration == copy.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration {\n        t.Error(\"DeepCopy did not create independent copy\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### CRD CRUD Operations\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeCRUD(t *testing.T) {\n    // Requires kubeconfig or mock client\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    namespace := \"default\"\n\n    // Create\n    agentRuntime := &AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n            SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n            Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n        },\n    }\n\n    created, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Read\n    fetched, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, created.Spec.MaxSessionDuration, fetched.Spec.MaxSessionDuration)\n\n    // Update\n    fetched.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration = 10 * time.Hour\n    updated, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, fetched, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, 10*time.Hour, updated.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration)\n\n    // Delete\n    err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n}\n```\n\n### Schema Validation\n\nVerify generated CRD YAML matches expected OpenAPI v3 schema:\n\n```bash\n# Generate CRDs\nmake gen-crd\n\n# Validate against sample resources\nkubectl apply --dry-run=server -f examples/agentruntime.yaml\nkubectl apply --dry-run=server -f examples/codeinterpreter.yaml\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Role |\n|---------|---------|------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | ^1.32 | PodSpec, core types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, conditions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/runtime` | ^0.17.2 | controller-gen markers |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/crd` | ^0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n\n## Build Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `make generate` | Run controller-gen to produce deepcopy functions |\n| `make gen-crd` | Generate CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n| `make gen-client` | Generate client-go to `client-go/` |\n| `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Verify types compile |","after":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- Go module path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs are defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`. These types enable the AgentCube control plane to manage sandbox runtime configurations programmatically through the Kubernetes API server.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────┐\n│   API Server        │      │   Workload Manager  │\n│                     │      │                     │\n│  ┌───────────────┐  │      │  ┌───────────────┐  │\n│  │ agentruntimes │  │◄─────│  │ CREATE/UPDATE │  │\n│  └───────────────┘  │      │  └───────────────┘  │\n│  ┌───────────────┐  │      └─────────────────────┘\n│  │codeinterpreters│ │\n│  └───────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────┘\n           │\n           ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐\n│   client-go         │\n│   (generated)       │\n│                     │\n│ - Typed clients     │\n│ - Listers           │\n│ - Informers         │\n└─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Package Structure\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `doc.go` | Package documentation, kubebuilder markers |\n| `groupversion_info.go` | GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder |\n| `register.go` | Kind constants, resource helpers |\n| `types.go` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n| `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | DeepCopy methods (generated) |\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec              AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status            AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n    PodTemplate *PodTemplateSpec `json:\"podTemplate,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreter\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec              CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status            CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    AuthMode *AuthMode `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n    SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n    Ports []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Template ContainerTemplateSpec `json:\"template\"`\n    WarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n    Ready bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Shared Types\n\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"` // HTTP or HTTPS\n    Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype PodTemplateSpec struct {\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec PodSpecSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype PodSpecSpec struct {\n    // Selective PodSpec fields: Containers, Volumes, ImagePullSecrets, etc.\n    // See proposal.md for full field list.\n}\n\ntype ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n    Image string `json:\"image\"`\n    Command []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n    Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n    Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n    RuntimeClassName *string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AuthMode string\n\nconst (\n    AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"\n    AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"\n)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `*metav1.Duration` | Yes | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `*metav1.Duration` | Yes | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout before cleanup |\n| `targetPort` | `[]TargetPort` | Yes | - | Port configuration array |\n| `podTemplate` | `*PodTemplateSpec` | No | - | Pod specification overrides |\n\n### CodeInterpreter\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `authMode` | `*AuthMode` | No | `\"picod\"` | Authentication mode: `picod`, `none` |\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `*metav1.Duration` | No | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `*metav1.Duration` | No | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout |\n| `ports` | `[]TargetPort` | No | - | Port configuration |\n| `template` | `ContainerTemplateSpec` | Yes | - | Container specification |\n| `warmPoolSize` | `*int32` | No | `0` | Pre-warmed pod count |\n\n### Status Subresource\n\nBoth CRDs support `/status` subresource:\n- `conditions`: Kubernetes conditions array\n- `observedGeneration`: Last reconciled generation\n\nCodeInterpreter additionally includes:\n- `ready`: Boolean readiness indicator\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### CRD Validation\n\nValidation rules embedded via kubebuilder markers:\n\n```go\n// Required field validation\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n\n// Default value handling\n// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n\n// Enum validation (AuthMode)\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n```\n\n### Client-go Error Handling\n\nStandard Kubernetes client errors are handled by client-go:\n\n| Error Type | Handling |\n|------------|----------|\n| `errors.IsNotFound` | Resource does not exist |\n| `errors.IsAlreadyExists` | Resource already exists |\n| `errors.IsConflict` | Optimistic lock failure |\n| `errors.IsTimeout` | Operation timeout |\n\nExample usage:\n\n```go\nagentRuntime, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\nif errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n    // Handle not found\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Type Validation\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeSpecValidation(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        spec    AgentRuntimeSpec\n        wantErr bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"valid spec with all required fields\",\n            spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n                SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n                Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n            },\n            wantErr: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"missing required maxSessionDuration\",\n            spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                SessionTimeout: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n                Ports:          []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n            },\n            wantErr: true,\n        },\n    }\n\n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            // Validate using Kubernetes validation webhook or custom validation\n            err := validateAgentRuntimeSpec(tt.spec)\n            if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n                t.Errorf(\"validateAgentRuntimeSpec() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### DeepCopy Verification\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n    original := &AgentRuntime{\n        Spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n            SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n            Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\"}},\n        },\n    }\n\n    copy := original.DeepCopy()\n\n    // Verify copy is independent\n    copy.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration = 10 * time.Hour\n\n    if original.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration == copy.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration {\n        t.Error(\"DeepCopy did not create independent copy\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### CRD CRUD Operations\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeCRUD(t *testing.T) {\n    // Requires kubeconfig or mock client\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    namespace := \"default\"\n\n    // Create\n    agentRuntime := &AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n            SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n            Ports:              []TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n        },\n    }\n\n    created, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Read\n    fetched, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, created.Spec.MaxSessionDuration, fetched.Spec.MaxSessionDuration)\n\n    // Update\n    fetched.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration = 10 * time.Hour\n    updated, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, fetched, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, 10*time.Hour, updated.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration)\n\n    // Delete\n    err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, \"test-runtime\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n}\n```\n\n### Schema Validation\n\nVerify generated CRD YAML matches expected OpenAPI v3 schema:\n\n```bash\n# Generate CRDs\nmake gen-crd\n\n# Validate against sample resources\nkubectl apply --dry-run=server -f examples/agentruntime.yaml\nkubectl apply --dry-run=server -f examples/codeinterpreter.yaml\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Role |\n|---------|---------|------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | ^1.32 | PodSpec, core types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, conditions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/runtime` | ^0.17.2 | controller-gen markers |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/crd` | ^0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n\n## Build Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `make generate` | Run controller-gen to produce deepcopy functions |\n| `make gen-crd` | Generate CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n| `make gen-client` | Generate client-go to `client-go/` |\n| `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Verify types compile |\n\n---\n\n# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-003 focuses on the shared types and constants used across AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. These shared definitions ensure consistency and reduce duplication across the API.\n\n## Module Structure\n\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n├── doc.go                    # Package documentation + kubebuilder markers\n├── register.go               # GroupVersion constants and scheme registration\n├── types.go                  # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, shared types)\n├── types_test.go             # Unit tests\n└── zz_generated.deepcopy.go  # Auto-generated deepcopy methods\n```\n\n## Shared Constants\n\n### Group Version\n\n```go\nconst (\n    GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n)\n\nvar SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: GroupName, Version: Version}\n```\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `GroupName` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | API group name |\n| `Version` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | API version |\n| `SchemeGroupVersion` | `schema.GroupVersion` | Combined GroupVersion for scheme registration |\n\n### Auth Modes\n\n```go\ntype AuthMode string\n\nconst (\n    AuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"  // picod authentication\n    AuthModeNone  AuthMode = \"none\"   // No authentication\n)\n```\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `AuthModePicod` | `\"picod\"` | Use picod for session authentication |\n| `AuthModeNone` | `\"none\"` | No authentication required |\n\n## Shared Types\n\n### TargetPort\n\nDefines port configuration for runtime services.\n\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    Port       int32  `json:\"port\"`        // Required: 1-65535\n    Protocol   string `json:\"protocol\"`    // Required: HTTP or HTTPS\n    Name       string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### PodTemplateSpec\n\nCustom pod template for runtime pods.\n\n```go\ntype PodTemplateSpec struct {\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec              *PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### PodSpec\n\nSelective subset of `corev1.PodSpec` for runtime customization.\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `Containers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Container specifications |\n| `Volumes` | `[]corev1.Volume` | Pod volumes |\n| `RestartPolicy` | `corev1.RestartPolicy` | Container restart policy |\n| `ServiceAccountName` | `string` | Service account for pods |\n| `NodeSelector` | `map[string]string` | Node selection criteria |\n| `Affinity` | `*corev1.Affinity` | Pod scheduling affinity |\n| `Tolerations` | `[]corev1.Toleration` | Node taint tolerations |\n| `PriorityClassName` | `string` | Priority class |\n| `Priority` | `*int32` | Priority value |\n| `DNSPolicy` | `corev1.DNSPolicy` | DNS configuration |\n| `HostNetwork` | `bool` | Use host network |\n| `HostPID` | `bool` | Use host PID namespace |\n| `HostIPC` | `bool` | Use host IPC namespace |\n| `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.PodSecurityContext` | Pod security context |\n| `ImagePullSecrets` | `[]corev1.LocalObjectReference` | Image pull secrets |\n| `InitContainers` | `[]ContainerSpec` | Init containers |\n\n### ContainerSpec\n\nSelective subset of `corev1.Container`.\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `Name` | `string` | Container name (Required) |\n| `Image` | `string` | Container image (Required) |\n| `Command` | `[]string` | Entrypoint command |\n| `Args` | `[]string` | Command arguments |\n| `Env` | `[]corev1.EnvVar` | Environment variables |\n| `Resources` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements` | Compute resources |\n| `ImagePullPolicy` | `corev1.PullPolicy` | Image pull policy |\n| `Ports` | `[]corev1.ContainerPort` | Exposed ports |\n| `LivenessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Liveness probe |\n| `ReadinessProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Readiness probe |\n| `StartupProbe` | `*corev1.Probe` | Startup probe |\n| `VolumeMounts` | `[]corev1.VolumeMount` | Volume mounts |\n| `SecurityContext` | `*corev1.SecurityContext` | Container security context |\n\n### ContainerTemplateSpec\n\nSimplified container spec for CodeInterpreter.\n\n```go\ntype ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n    Image            string                    `json:\"image\"` // Required\n    Command          []string                  `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n    Args             []string                  `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    Env              []corev1.EnvVar           `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n    Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n    RuntimeClassName *string                   `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n## Scheme Registration\n\n### Resource Helper\n\n```go\nfunc Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource {\n    return SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(resource).GroupResource()\n}\n```\n\nReturns `GroupResource` for RBAC and storage configuration.\n\n### Type Registration\n\n```go\nfunc AddKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n    scheme.AddKnownTypes(SchemeGroupVersion,\n        &AgentRuntime{},\n        &AgentRuntimeList{},\n        &CodeInterpreter{},\n        &CodeInterpreterList{},\n    )\n    metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n## Default Values\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Applied By |\n|-------|------|---------|------------|\n| `MaxSessionDuration` | `string` | `\"8h\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n| `SessionTimeout` | `string` | `\"15m\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n| `AuthMode` | `AuthMode` | `\"picod\"` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n| `WarmPoolSize` | `int32` | `0` | Kubernetes defaulting |\n\n## Usage by CRDs\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n- Uses: `TargetPort`, `PodTemplateSpec`, `PodSpec`, `ContainerSpec`\n- Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`\n\n### CodeInterpreter\n\n- Uses: `TargetPort`, `ContainerTemplateSpec`, `AuthMode`\n- Constants: `GroupName`, `Version`, `SchemeGroupVersion`, `AuthModePicod`, `AuthModeNone`\n\n## Code Generation\n\nTypes are annotated with kubebuilder markers for code generation:\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n```\n\n| Marker | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `+genclient` | Generate typed client |\n| `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` | Generate list type |\n| `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` | Enable status subresource |\n| `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName` | CLI short name |\n| `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` | Custom columns |\n\n## Validation\n\nShared types use kubebuilder validation markers:\n\n| Validation | Marker | Applied To |\n|------------|--------|------------|\n| Required | `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` | Port, Protocol, Image |\n| Pattern | `+kubebuilder:validation:Pattern` | Duration strings |\n| Enum | `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum` | AuthMode, Protocol |\n| Range | `+kubebuilder:validation:Minimum/Maximum` | Port number |\n| MinItems | `+kubebuilder:validation:MinItems` | TargetPorts array |","additions":219,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775840867753,"end":1775840867794}}}}
